NORMALISED EXTRACT:
Signature: Number.isInteger(value) -> boolean
Definition: returns true iff typeof value === 'number', value is finite, and value is mathematically an integer (no fractional part). Implementation equivalently: typeof value === 'number' && isFinite(value) && Math.floor(value) === value.
Special cases: NaN and Infinity return false. -0 is considered an integer and returns true. BigInt values return false (different primitive type).

