1. API signature
Number.isInteger(value: any): boolean

2. Semantics and algorithm
- Coerce: no coercion of non-number types; typeof must be 'number'.
- Check finiteness: reject NaN, Infinity, -Infinity.
- Check integer: floor(value) === value (or value % 1 === 0).

3. Edge cases and examples
Number.isInteger(3) -> true
Number.isInteger(3.0) -> true
Number.isInteger(3.1) -> false
Number.isInteger(NaN) -> false
Number.isInteger(Infinity) -> false
Number.isInteger('3') -> false
Number.isInteger(-0) -> true

4. Polyfill and compatibility
Polyfill (equivalent behavior):
Number.isInteger = Number.isInteger || function(value) { return typeof value === 'number' && isFinite(value) && Math.floor(value) === value; };

5. Supplementary implementation details
Use when validating API inputs that must be integer numbers. Avoid using global isFinite without typeof check since non-numeric coercion may lead to wrong results.

